143
00:07:35.710 --> 00:07:36.400
Right?

144
00:07:36.400 --> 00:07:40.250
So, often you have multiple
different attributes of people.

145
00:07:40.250 --> 00:07:43.540
So, they vary on their education,

146
00:07:43.540 --> 00:07:47.800
their experience levels,
what it was they were doing.

147
00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:51.089
So, we see their friendliness, their
helpfulness, all of these sorts of things.

148
00:07:51.089 --> 00:07:55.480
And the challenge is if you just
look at one of these variables,

149
00:07:55.480 --> 00:07:57.320
is it that that's predicting performance,
or

150
00:07:57.320 --> 00:08:00.090
is it just that it's highly
correlated with something else.

151
00:08:00.090 --> 00:08:02.870
You wanna disentangle those
influences to make sure you really

152
00:08:02.870 --> 00:08:05.680
are getting at the attributes
that drive performance.

153
00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:09.660
One of the things you wanna do there
as well is probable just apply a bit of

154
00:08:09.660 --> 00:08:10.350
common sense.

